Ask HN: Are Startups Getting Stuck in an AI Paralysis?
text:
The recent groundbreaking advances in AI (mainly by OpenAI) have created so much volatility that it’s very hard to estimate a clear strategic path. What seems like a good idea today could be obsolete in a month.

It looks like ChatGPT is becoming the main interface for executing varous tasks like search, bookings, shopping.

Maybe I'm overreacting, but I'm seeing many overwhelmed founders desperately trying to keep up with the innovation pace. Bigger companies are getting FOMO and are trying to integrate AI into all their products.
